- 'Underdogs' refers to teams that are less successful or have a lower ranking compared to their competitors;
- 'Cumulative distribution' is a statistical measure that shows the proportion of data points that fall below a given value;
- 'Bottom half' means the teams that are in the lower 50% of the cumulative distribution.

